      Deprecated

      The third parameter of sqliteTable is changing and will only accept an array instead of an object

      Example

      Deprecated version:

      export const users = sqliteTable("users", {
      	id: int(),
      }, (t) => ({
      	idx: index('custom_name').on(t.id)
      }));

      New API:

      export const users = sqliteTable("users", {
      	id: int(),
      }, (t) => [
      	index('custom_name').on(t.id)
      ]);

      Deprecated

      The third parameter of sqliteTable is changing and will only accept an array instead of an object

      Example

      Deprecated version:

      export const users = sqliteTable("users", {
      	id: int(),
      }, (t) => ({
      	idx: index('custom_name').on(t.id)
      }));

      New API:

      export const users = sqliteTable("users", {
      	id: int(),
      }, (t) => [
      	index('custom_name').on(t.id)
      ]);
